subsection.def:
conference
                    (公會) has the meaning given to that term by
                Chapter I of the Code;

paragraph.content:
the documents to be produced and the matters to be proved by a person
                    seeking recognition of a recommendation or enforcement of a recommendation,
                    determination or award;

subparagraph.content:
the principle that conference practices should not involve any
                    discrimination against the shipowners, shippers or the foreign trade of any
                    country;

a list of cargo, which may include bulk cargo shipped without mark
                            or count, which is specifically excluded from the scope of the loyalty
                            arrangement;

a definition of the circumstances in which cargo other than cargo
                            covered by (i) above is considered to be excluded from the scope of the
                            loyalty arrangement;

freight rates shall be fixed at as low a level as is feasible from the
                        commercial point of view and shall permit a reasonable profit for
                        shipowners;

in disputes relating to general freight-rate increases: not later than
                        the date of expiry of the period of notice specified in Article
                        14(1);

a conference or a shippers’ organization may institute proceedings as a
                        party or be named as a party to proceedings in its collective
                        capacity;

any notification to a conference or shippers’ organization in its
                        collective capacity shall also constitute a notification to each member of
                        such conference or shippers’ organization;

no member of the Panel of conciliators having the same nationality as
                        either of the two appointed conciliators shall be eligible for selection by
                        lot;

any party which accepted the recommendation was, under the law
                        applicable to it, under some legal incapacity at the time of
                        acceptance;

the party or parties rejecting the recommendation shall publish its or
                        their grounds for rejection, given pursuant to Article 37(3), and may at the
                        same time publish the recommendation and the reasons therefor;

maintain the list of conciliators of the International Panel of
                        Conciliators and regularly inform the Contracting Parties of the composition
                        of the Panel;

receive and maintain copies of requests for conciliation, replies,
                        recommendations, acceptances, or rejections, including reasons
                        therefor;

furnish on request, and at their cost, copies of recommendations and
                        reasons for rejection to the shippers’ organizations, conferences and
                        governments, subject to the provisions of Article 40;

state whether an oral hearing is desired and, if so, and to the extent
                        then known, the names and addresses of persons to give evidence, including
                        experts’ evidence, for the claimant;

be accompanied by such supporting documentation and relevant agreements
                        and arrangements entered into by the parties as the claimant may consider
                        necessary at the time of making the claim;

state whether an oral hearing is desired and, if so, and to the extent
                        then known, the names and addresses of persons to give evidence, including
                        experts’ evidence, for the respondent;

be accompanied by such supporting documentation and relevant agreements
                        and arrangements entered into by the parties as the respondent may consider
                        necessary at the time of making the reply;

subsection.def:
conference
                        (公會) has the meaning given by Chapter I
                    of the Code;

person
                        (人) includes an unincorporated
                    conference;

subparagraph.content:
“SD” in column 2 of the Table shall be a statutory duty enforceable
                        only at the suit of any person mentioned in column 4 of the Table against
                        any person listed in column 5;

paragraph.content:
the two groups of national shipping lines will co-ordinate their position
                    before voting on matters concerning the trade between their two countries;
                    and

subsection.def:
conference
                        (公會) has the meaning given by Chapter I
                    of the Code;

shipper
                        (托運人) has the meaning given by Chapter I
                    of the Code;
